All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
AppState
The AppState class represents the current state of the Zello Work app.
Audio
Manages AudioMode used by Zello Work app.
AudioMode
The AudioMode enum represents the audio modes available with Zello SDK.
BluetoothAccessoryState
The BluetoothAccessoryState enum represents states of Bluetooth accessories.
BluetoothAccessoryType
The BluetoothAccessoryType enum represents types of Bluetooth accessories.
Contact
The Contact class represents a contact of the current user.
Contacts
The Contacts class represents the contacts of the current user.
ContactStatus
The ContactStatus enum represents the status of a Contact.
ContactType
The ContactType enum represents the type of Contact.
Error
The Error enum represents some of the authentication errors that can be encountered in the Zello SDK.
Events
The Events interface enables monitoring of Zello SDK state and property changes
MessageIn
The MessageIn class represents an incoming voice message.
MessageOut
The MessageOut class represents an outgoing voice message.
PermissionError
The PermissionError enum defines permission-related errors.
SafeHandler<T extends SafeHandlerEvents>
Handler wrapper that prevents a potential memory leak occurring due to a raw Handler being a member of a service or an activity.
SafeHandlerEvents
Callback events used with SafeHandler.
Status
The Status enum represents the status of the current user.
Tab
The Tab enum represents the contact selection UI tabs of the Zello Work app.
Theme
The Theme enum represents the UI themes available for contact selection UI.
Zello
The Zello singleton acts as the primary point of interacting to the Zello SDK.
